<h2 id="guidelines">Guidelines</h2>
<h3 id="line-length">Characters per line</h3>
<p>It is recommend that lines of text be no more than 65-75 characters, including spaces (<span class="fnt-italic">Designing With Type</span>, James Craig). This makes for a more comfortable reading experience. Usability studies dating back to the 1970's show readers experience fatigue with text running longer than this.</p>
<p>To demonstrate, the paragraph above has no width limit while that same paragraph below maxes out at <span class="fnt-bold">75ch</span> using the <code>txt-maxlength</code> utility class:</p>
<p style="max-width: 600px">It is recommend that lines of text be no more than 65-75 characters, including spaces (<span class="fnt-italic">Designing With Type</span>, James Craig). This makes for a more comfortable reading experience. Usability studies dating back to the 1970's show readers experience fatigue with text running longer than this.</p>
<h3 id="seo">SEO</h3>
<p>Using these text semantically will improve SEO and accessibility.</p>
<h3 id="a11y">Accessibility</h3>
<p>The smallest font size that Mdash has is 13px, which is the smallest recommended by WCAG 2.1. Any smaller can be illegible for some users.</p>
